I have an airspeed indicator in my bus. that way i can get my true airspeed 
through the air, compare it to groundspeed off of the speedo, pull out my 
E6B flight computer, find out how much wind correction angle i need to put 
in to stay on course. I also have an altimeter and vertical speed indicator 
so i can figure out my true aispeed from calibrated, then use the VSI to 
vary my decent rate down those arkansas hills. hehehe!
if there are any pilots on this board they will understand.
john

